Foot and mouth disease, China (People's Rep. of)
-----------------------------------------
Information received on 16 Apr 2013 from Dr Zhang Zhongqui, Director General, China Animal Disease Control Centre, Veterinary Bureau, Ministry of Agriculture, Beijing, China (People's Rep. of)

Summary
Report type: Immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 8 Apr 2013
Date of pre-confirmation of the event: 15 Apr 2013
Report date: 16 Apr 2013
Date submitted to OIE: 16 Apr 2013
Reason for notification: Reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: January 2010
Manifestation of disease: Clinical disease
Causal agent: Foot and mouth disease virus
Serotype: A
Nature of diagnosis: Suspicion, Clinical, Laboratory (basic), Laboratory (advanced)
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country.

New outbreaks (1)
Outbreak 1: Hailipaiquke Village, Luopu, Hetian, XINJIANG
Date of start of the outbreak: 8 Apr 2013
Outbreak status: Continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: Farm
Affected animals
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Cattle / 12 / 12 / 0 / 12 / 0

Summary of outbreaks
Total outbreaks: 1
Total animals affected
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Cattle / 12 / 12 / 0 / 12 / 0

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: Unknown or inconclusive

Control measures
Measures applied: Stamping out; Quarantine; Movement control inside the country; Screening; Zoning; Disinfection of infected premises/establishment(s); Dipping/Spraying; No vaccination; No treatment of affected animals

Measures to be applied: No other measures

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type: Lanzhou Veterinary Research Institute (National Laboratory) (OIE's Reference Laboratory)

Species / Test / Test date / Result
Cattle / enzyme-linked immunosorbent assay (ELISA) / 15 Apr 2013 / Positive
Cattle / reverse transcription-polymerase chain reaction (RT-PCR) / 15 Apr 2013 / Positive
Cattle / virus isolation / 15 Apr 2013 / Positive

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[On 18 Mar 2013, China reported to the OIE an outbreak of FMD serotype A in cattle in the Chengbei district, Xining, Qinghai. Reportedly, the reason for the said notification was: "New strain of a listed disease." It was controlled by stamping out (destruction of all 63 cattle in the affected herd where 2 cases were reported, no mortality.

The said and an earlier FMDV serotype A outbreak during 2013 in China have been described in posting 20130319.1594167. Genotyping results are anticipated. - Mod.AS

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: http://healthmap.org/r/1zaU.]
